In summary, the controllable synthesis of MnOOH nanomaterials was achieved via a simple solvothermal reaction. MnOOH nanomaterials with nanowire, nanonet, and nanorod structures were obtained under room temperature, 180°C, and 220°C, respectively. Then, the three distinct MnOOH materials were used as substrates for the polymerization of aniline. The obtained PANI/MnOOH nanocomposites were applied for electrocatalytic oxidations of DA. PANI/n-MnOOH
